This paper is primarily focused on improving the accuracy and efficiency of video recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The proposed method involves using multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using various baseline methods and achieving state-of-the-art results, which suggests that it could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories as well.
